To normalize the provided profile data according to the specified guidelines, I'll follow the normalization instructions for each relevant field. Here's how the process would look for a given input profile:

### Example Input Profile
```json
{
  "name": "Jane Doe",
  "title": "Sr. Software Eng.",
  "location": "San Francisco, CA",
  "key_skills": [
    "Python",
    "Data Analysis",
    "AWS"
  ],
  "experience": [
    {
      "company": "Tech Solutions Inc.",
      "title": "Software Engineer",
      "duration": {
        "start_date": "March 2018",
        "end_date": "June 2021",
        "date_range": "3 years 3 months"
      },
      "location": "San Francisco Bay Area"
    },
    {
      "company": "Innovatech",
      "title": "Lead Developer",
      "duration": {
        "start_date": "July 2021",
        "end_date": "Present",
        "date_range": "2 years"
      },
      "location": "Remote"
    }
  ]
}
```

### Normalized Output Profile
```json
{
  "name": "Jane Doe",
  "title": "Senior Software Engineer",
  "location": "San Francisco, California, United States",
  "key_skills": [
    "Python",
    "Data Analysis",
    "Amazon Web Services"
  ],
  "experience": [
    {
      "company": "Tech Solutions Inc.",
      "title": "Software Engineer",
      "duration": {
        "start_date": "2018-03",
        "end_date": "2021-06",
        "date_range": "3 years 3 months"
      },
      "location": "San Francisco, California, United States"
    },
    {
      "company": "Innovatech",
      "title": "Lead Developer",
      "duration": {
        "start_date": "2021-07",
        "end_date": "Present",
        "date_range": "2 years"
      },
      "location": "Remote"
    }
  ],
  "normalization_notes": "Standardized location to full city and state name; Expanded AWS to Amazon Web Services; Converted date formats to ISO."
}
```

### Explanation of Changes
1. **Title Normalization**: "Sr. Software Eng." was expanded to "Senior Software Engineer".
2. **Location Normalization**: "San Francisco, CA" was expanded to "San Francisco, California, United States".
3. **Skills Normalization**: "AWS" was expanded to "Amazon Web Services".
4. **Experience Location Normalization**: "San Francisco Bay Area" was standardized to "San Francisco, California, United States".
5. **Date Normalization**: Dates were converted to ISO format (e.g., "March 2018" to "2018-03").
6. **Normalization Notes**: Added a note to document significant changes and expansions.

This process ensures that the profile data is consistent and standardized, facilitating better analysis and clustering in downstream applications.
